Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Normandy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Normandy in northern France. This surname is now rare in Britain.","Americanized form of French   Normandin  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Normandin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Alain, Serge, Adrien, Andre, Aurore, Celine, Clovis, Emile, Gaetan, Gilles, Laurier.","French: from a diminutive of   Normand  . Compare   Normandy  ."]}]},{"name":"Olga","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["name of Scandinavian origin, originally derived from the Old Norse adjective <i>heilagr</i> ‘prosperous, successful’. It was imported by the Scandinavian settlers who founded the first Russian state in the 9th century.  St Olga  of Kiev (  d. 969 ) was a Varangian noblewoman who was baptized at Byzantium in about  957  and set about converting her people. The name was introduced to the English-speaking world in the late 19th century, but retains a distinctively Russian flavour."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Olga de Normandy was born in 1015, in Frémontiers, Somme, Picardie, France. She married Sir Walter de Tyrell I  Lord of Poix about 1030. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in Poix, Somme, Picardie, France."},"et":{"1015–":"1015–Surnud","1015–1068":"1015–1068","1006–Male":"1006–Surnud","1040–1066":"1040–1066","1035–1069":"1035–1069","–Male":"Surnud","1015–Female":"1015–Surnud","about 1030":"umbes 1030","1006":"1006","about